      <section eId="sec_204_G">
        <num>204-G</num>
        <heading>Restrictions on the use of firefighting foam containing PFAS chemicals</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_204_G__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>"Class B firefighting foam" means foams designed to extinguish\nignitable liquid fires.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_204_G__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>"Ignitable liquid fire" shall have the same meaning as defined in\nparagraph</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_204_G__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>of subdivision one of section three hundred ninety-one-u\nof the general business law.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_204_G__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>"Local governments" includes any county, city, town, village, fire\ndistrict, fire company as defined in section two hundred four-a of this\narticle, regional fire protection authority, or other special purpose\ndistrict that provides firefighting services.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_204_G__subsec_d">
          <num>(d)</num>
          <content>
            <p>"Perfluoroalkyl and polyfluoroalkyl substances" or "PFAS\nchemicals" shall have the same meaning as defined in paragraph</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_204_G__subsec_f">
          <num>(f)</num>
          <content>
            <p>of\nsubdivision one of section three hundred ninety-one-u of the general\nbusiness law.\n  2. No local government shall discharge or otherwise use for training\npurposes class B firefighting foam that contains intentionally added\nperfluoroalkyl and polyfluoroalkyl substances (PFAS chemicals).\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
